In a brief exchange with reporters, President Biden stated that he is feeling great and has tested negative for COVID-19. He expressed optimism about the inflation bill, saying it will immediately help Americans, particularly seniors on Medicare who will have a cap of $2,000 for drug bills. He believes the bill will be game-changing for ordinary people and will lower medical expenses. When asked about the situation in Taiwan, the President expressed concern about China's actions but stated that he doesn't think they will escalate further. He also commented that Speaker Pelosi's decision to visit Taiwan was her own.